        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 12:00AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles southeast of Utopia, or 14 miles southwest of Tarpley, moving
north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tarpley, Utopia, Medina, Vanderpool, and Lost Maples State Natural
Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
